originalText.text:
Unique concept for wraps under $15 with lots of vegetarian friendly options. Would definitely suggest their Dire wolf bowl(pay a little extra to convert a wrap to a bowl and substitute the salad with quinoa). Food was really tasty. Will visit again to taste other items on the menu.

Only issue I had with the place is limited indoor seating which I know can’t be changed easily. There is some outdoor seating available but would be a little uncomfortable during the summer days. But worth it if you want to have your food warm and fresh instead of a takeaway

originalText.text: Very unique experience, watching them press the wrap and then heat it up it in front of you. Wrap was very good, lot of flavors. kind of small for $15, and no sides included. Service is pretty slow and they really didn’t explain much just stared at me while I made a decision. Its a very small dine in area but there’s some outdoor sheds if you like that. I got the dire wolf wrap which I recommend. next time I’d like to try it in a bowl but I really enjoyed the flavor of the wrap.

originalText.text:
Unique, flavorful and delicious filling wraps and bowls for under $15. You can swap greens for quinoa for $1 which is a pretty good deal. They have a few vegetarian/vegan options as well. They have a good amount of outdoor seating and some indoor seating. Would definitely be back.

We got the Direwolf (chicken with lamb bacon) wrap and the brothers Grimm bowl (grilled chicken  with pickled shitake mushrooms). Both of them were great and were quite filling.

Woof Wraps is now my top spot for wraps. While their menu isn't expansive, it has all the proteins I crave (chicken breast, lamb and shrimp) and has an excellent array of toppings. What's more, their selection of tortillas is quite diverse, ranging from whole grain to corn and even options with turmeric.

The interior design of the establishment is minimalistic but captivating. Brickwork and art featuring fiery themes, create an engaging ambiance. The process of preparation deserves mentioning - they have an “iron wolf” - a scorching-hot metal surface they use to squeeze and fry the tortilla. Witnessing it is truly a spectacle!

Woof Wraps goes beyond the ordinary by serving remarkably generous portions - they are larger than my face! Just a few bites into one of their wraps, and you'll feel satisfyingly satiated (i usually have enough for 2-3 meals).

My favorite order is The Beast with half the cheese (I watch my calories). It is a delightful medley of savory chicken breast, fresh vegetables and an array of flavorful sauces. On top there’s some (secret) crunch. While I'm not usually a fan of sauces, I must admit that their skillful incorporation has won me over completely.

I hold a special affection for their wraps, and I'm confident you'll feel the same way once you give them a try.

originalText.text: OMG the best wrap I’ve ever had! the freshly pressed and fired wrap made such a difference. we got the direwolf and the pack. both were excellent- the pack was more of a breakfast burrito & the direwolf was fried chicken with cabbage and lamb bacon. this is a great spot for anyone who doesn’t eat pork & there are vegan/vegetarian options too. the sauces were also stellar- the wolfnights ketchup is a must.
